# Bug flow (spec-lifecycle.md §8): `type: bug` in proposal.md's
# frontmatter selects the repro/fix stage set (not refine/design/plan);
# repro needs no specs/ delta; fix's tasks.md is optional.

env HOME=/no-home

exec lifecycle approve --stage repro 007-fix-panic
stdout 'approve: approved stage "repro" for 007-fix-panic \(1 artifact\(s\) hashed\)'

exec lifecycle status --change 007-fix-panic
stdout '007-fix-panic \(bug\)'
stdout 'repro    approved'
stdout 'fix      pending'
! stdout 'refine'
! stdout 'design'
! stdout 'plan '

-- lifecycle.yml --
schemaVersion: 1
consentPolicy: off

-- openspec/changes/007-fix-panic/proposal.md --
---
issue: "kentra-io/kafka-dq#7"
type: bug
---

# Fix panic on empty input

Repro: `TestParseEmptyInput` in parser_test.go currently panics; should
return a ParseError instead.
